>
	<p>
		I'm James Jenkins. I've spent 20+ years building and leading businesses at the
		intersection of technology, creativity and commercial growth &mdash; from London to
		San Francisco, New York, and now Stockholm.
	</p>

	<p>
		Today I'm Group CEO of Forsman &amp; Bodenfors across Sweden, the UK and Ireland, leading
		the organisation with full P&amp;L responsibility and a portfolio that includes Barilla,
		SKF, Volvo Cars, and Supercell. In 2025 I was promoted to European CEO within Stagwell's
		network. The job is integration: bringing strategy, creative, product and operations
		together so that financial performance and creative work both get better.
	</p>

	<p>
		Before that I was Global COO of B-Reel, scaling the business across six markets in the US
		and Europe &mdash; partnering with Google, Nike, LVMH, Activision Blizzard and H&amp;M, and
		earning recognition from Fast Company, AdWeek and Ad Age. I started out at AKQA when
		digital marketing was still emerging, spending eight years leading the global Nike
		relationship and major launches with Microsoft and Xbox, through the agency's rise to
		Ad Age 'Agency of the Decade'.
	</p>

	<p>
		That early experience shaped how I approach change: move early, stay curious, build
		advantage through innovation. I care deeply about the people I work with. We only get one
		go at this &mdash; so we might as well build something great and have fun doing it.
	</p>
</Layout>